# Git workflow — App Review Monitoring

Aligned with [masterfabric-mac-cli](https://github.com/gurkanfikretgunak/masterfabric-mac-cli) (`AGENTS.md`, `release-workflow.mdc`).

## Branch naming

Use a short prefix + kebab-case slug:

| Prefix | Use |
|--------|-----|
| `feat/` | New feature or UI capability |
| `fix/` | Bug fix |
| `chore/` | Tooling, rules, deps, docs-only maintenance |
| `docs/` | Documentation-only (optional; `chore:` commits also OK) |

Examples:

- `feat/rich-result-monitoring`
- `fix/grafana-kpi-query`
- `chore/cursor-rules-agents-md`

Work on `main` only for tiny hotfixes when the user explicitly asks.

## Commit messages (English, Conventional Commits)

Format:

```text
<type>(<scope>): <short imperative summary>
```

- **type:** `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`
- **scope (optional):** `frontend`, `backend`, `deploy`, `grafana`, `mlc`
- **summary:** lowercase-ish, imperative, no trailing period preferred
- Optional body paragraph for *why* (still English)

Examples (from masterfabric-mac-cli style):

```text
feat(frontend): rich result UI and expanded LLM monitoring dashboard
fix(grafana): use increase() for analyze success rate KPI
chore: add AGENTS.md and Cursor project rules
docs(deploy): document inferreview.com Cloudflare tunnel routes
```

## Delivery loop (non-trivial changes)

1. Create or switch to `feat/…` / `fix/…` branch.
2. Commit with a clear English message (one logical change per commit when practical).
3. **Push** the branch: `git push -u origin HEAD`
4. Open PR with `gh pr create` — **English** title + body:

```markdown
## Summary
- …

## Test plan
- [ ] …
```

5. Do **not** push directly to `main` or change Render/Vercel env unless the user asks.

## Do not

- Auto-deploy or change production env vars without explicit approval.
- Commit `.env.hybrid`, `.env.prod`, API keys, or tunnel tokens.
- Write commit messages or PR bodies in Turkish (chat may stay Turkish).
- Skip branch workflow for multi-file features.

## After merge (optional)

Ask whether to deploy or tag — this repo has no semver `VERSION` file unless the user adds release tagging later.
